doctest
------------------------------------------
doctest is a new C++ testing framework but is by far the fastest both in
compile times (by orders of magnitude) and runtime compared to other
feature-rich alternatives. It brings the ability of compiled languages such as
D / Rust / Nim to have tests written directly in the production code thanks to
a fast, transparent and flexible test runner with a clean interface.

Runtime requirements:

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.40-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.36.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/doctest/doctest

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/doctest/doctest/archive/refs/tags/v2.4.11.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack doctest-2.4.11-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./doctest-2.4.11-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/doctest-2.4.11-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/doctest-2.4.11-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(doctest)
  /usr/include/doctest/doctest.h
  /usr/include/doctest/extensions/doctest_mpi.h
  /usr/include/doctest/extensions/doctest_util.h
  /usr/include/doctest/extensions/mpi_reporter.h
  /usr/include/doctest/extensions/mpi_sub_comm.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/doctest/doctest.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/doctest/doctestAddTests.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/doctest/doctestConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/doctest/doctestConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/doctest/doctestTargets.cmake
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/doctest.README
  /usr/share/doc/doctest/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/doctest/README.md

